However, a court can give a man the divorce papers if it proves that the marriage is not happy, or in case of a physical attack. Overall, the divorce rate in Montenegro is close to 3%. This happens due to the outdated views cited above and due to the fact that more and more people do not want to stay in outdated marriages.

A few things should be mentioned here. The main reason for divorce in Montenegro is the lack of an understanding between two people and such misunderstanding is caused by incompatible values and personalities. Another reason is unfaithfulness. However, a general reason for divorce in Montenegro is a feeling of love indifference that later turns into hatred.

If a person wants to get divorced in Montenegro, he or she should visit the court and make an application. When one side has an attorney, the matter becomes more complicated. In some cases, the divorce meets some rejections. The main reason for a rejection is the absence of the proper papers, pieces of evidence, and facts.
